[center][size=5][b]RenoDX — HDR and Color Grading[/b][/size]
Adds HDR output and full color grading controls to Greedfall 2.
Uses the ReShade Add-on API to rewrite the game's DX12 final output shader — this is NOT a ReShade effect.[/center]

[line]

[size=4][b]Features[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][b]HDR output[/b] — scRGB swapchain upgrade for true HDR signal to your display
[*][b]RenoDRT tonemapping[/b] — highlight expansion with adjustable peak brightness
[*][b]Full color grading[/b] — exposure, contrast, saturation, shadows, highlight saturation, blowout, flare, hue shift
[*][b]Color temperature[/b] — warm/cool white balance adjustment
[*][b]Shadow lift[/b] — raises black floor to reveal detail in dark areas
[*][b]Scene grading control[/b] — dial back or strengthen the game's original color grading
[*][b]UI intact[/b] — game HUD and menus remain fully functional
[/list]

[line]

[size=4][b]How It Works[/b][/size]
The game's swapchain is upgraded to 16-bit float (scRGB). The final output shader is replaced to decode the game's SDR signal to linear, expand the dynamic range, and apply RenoDRT tonemapping with your configured peak brightness. Highlights are expanded into HDR while midtones and shadows are preserved.

[line]

[size=4][b]Requirements[/b][/size]
[list]
[*]Windows HDR enabled in Display Settings
[*]HDR-capable display
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/site/mods/1710]RHI (ReShade HDR Installer)[/url] — installs ReShade automatically for you
[/list]
Also works with traditional ReShade installs — just place the addon DLL in the game directory alongside ReShade.

[line]

[size=4][b]Installation[/b][/size]

[b]With RHI (recommended):[/b]
[list=1]
[*]Download and run [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/site/mods/1710]RHI[/url] to install ReShade for Greedfall 2
[*]Drag [b]renodx-greedfall2.addon64[/b] into RHI to install the mod
[*]Launch the game
[*]Press [b]Home[/b] to open the ReShade overlay, navigate to the RenoDX tab
[*]Set Peak Brightness to match your display's peak nits
[/list]

[b]With traditional ReShade:[/b]
[list=1]
[*]Install [url=https://reshade.me/]ReShade[/url] for Greedfall 2 (select DirectX 12, enable addon support)
[*]Copy [b]renodx-greedfall2.addon64[/b] to the game folder (same folder as GreedFall2.exe)
[*]Launch the game
[*]Press [b]Home[/b] to open the ReShade overlay, navigate to the RenoDX tab
[*]Set Peak Brightness to match your display's peak nits
[/list]

[line]

[size=4][b]Uninstallation[/b][/size]

[b]With RHI:[/b] Remove the mod through RHI.
[b]With traditional ReShade:[/b] Delete [b]renodx-greedfall2.addon64[/b] from the game folder.

[line]

[size=4][b]Settings Guide[/b][/size]

[b]Tone Mapping[/b]
[list]
[*][b]Tone Mapper[/b] — Vanilla (original look), None, ACES, or RenoDRT
[*][b]Peak Brightness[/b] — Set to your display's peak nits (e.g. 780, 1000, 1400)
[*][b]Game Brightness[/b] — SDR reference white level (default 203 nits)
[/list]

[b]Color Grading[/b]
[list]
[*][b]Exposure[/b] — Overall brightness multiplier
[*][b]Contrast[/b] — Midtone contrast
[*][b]Saturation[/b] — Global color intensity
[*][b]Shadows[/b] — Shadow tone adjustment
[*][b]Highlight Saturation[/b] — Color intensity in bright areas
[*][b]Blowout[/b] — Highlight desaturation from overexposure
[*][b]Flare[/b] — Glare compensation
[*][b]Color Temperature[/b] — Warm/cool white balance shift
[*][b]Shadow Lift[/b] — Raises black floor to reveal shadow detail
[*][b]Scene Grading[/b] — Strength of the game's original color grading
[/list]

[line]

